  "texts": [
    "If we identify AE 0 (X) * = Lip 0 (X) and AE b (x) * = Lip b (X), then the span of evaluation functionals is dense in both ϵ(AE 0 (X)) and ϵ(AE b (X)).",
    "In either of the spaces Lip 0 (X) or Lip b (X) a sequence converges weak * if and only if it is bounded and it converges pointwise.Proposition 2.9.",
    "If X is compact, then ϵ(AE b (X)) = D 0 (X).Proof.",
    "For any Banach space B, we recall the basic fact:ϵ(B) = {φ ∈ B * *: φ acts weak * continuously on B * }.Since X is compact, by applying this fact to B = AE b (X), we conclude that ϵ(AE b (X)) is the set of those mapsT: Lip c (X) = Lip b (X) → R,which are linear and weak * continuous.",
    "By the Kreǐn-Shmul'yan theorem [13, Chapter 5, 12.1], weak * continuity is in this case equivalent to weak * sequential continuity."
